    {
      "topic": "Additional advice",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "When choosing connecting international flights, choose ones that are at least three hours in between of each other, as unexpected delays might force you to re-book your flight. In my case, I had a 24-hour layover in LAX because there was only a single flight to New Zealand available every day."
        },
        {
          "title": "Always pack the important stuff inside your carry-on luggage (e.g. passport, prescription medication)."
        },
        {
          "title": "It's good to have at least one set of clothes and underwear in your carry-on in case you get laid over for more than 12 hours and would rather leave your checked-in luggage at the airport."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
